parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power brake booster can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to extended stopping distances and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
and the ABS system fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the wheels to lock up, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS system fails to engage
the wheels lock up
the brake pedal goes to the floor
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A brake fluid leak can cause the brakes to fail, leading to extended stopping distances and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid is leaking from the vehicle
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal going to the floor can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
and the ABS system fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent brake failure can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brakes fail intermittently
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of power, inability to shift gears, and even lead to accidents, fires, and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle loses power
unable to shift gears
transmission slips or hesitates
transmission catches on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling line failure can cause transmission fluid to leak out, leading to transmission failure and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaks out
cooling line rusts off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Drive shaft failure can cause accidents and loss of control.
symptoms: Drive shaft falls off
vehicle loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stick shift location can pose a danger to the center passenger in the event of a collision or high-speed stop, potentially causing critical head injury.
symptoms: Stick shift location poses a danger to the center passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Movement When Starting/Turning Off Ignition
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle movement when starting or turning off the ignition can cause accidents or injuries, especially if the vehicle is on an incline.
symptoms: Vehicle moves forward when starting or turning off the ignition
even when the foot is on the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The buildup of carbon in the EGR valve can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of brake function, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine quits when decelerating to stop
the brakes give out
the engine stalls
the vehicle requires frequent restarting or coasting into stops.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Cooler Line Hose Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine oil cooler line hose can cause oil leakage, which can lead to engine damage and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Oil leakage
engine damage
brake failure (due to proximity of brake lines to oil cooler lines).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Radiator failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Engine overheating
coolant leakage
engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of valve guides and seals can cause engine damage, leading to engine failure and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Engine damage
engine failure
loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold can cause carbon monoxide to leak into the passenger compartment, posing a health risk to occupants.
symptoms: Carbon monoxide leakage into the passenger compartment
exhaust manifold hole or crack.
